[18:11:25] {"event": "tool_call", "tool": "think", "args": {"thought": "\nThe failures in the JSON report differ from the `--reporter=list` run (which showed 84 passed). This is because the JSON report run is a SEPARATE execution — and in this run:\n1. TC-83227 (edge) failed again with 45_000ms timeout on headings matching\n2. TC-83228 (edge) failed again with 45_000ms timeout on storesLink  \n3. FTC_02_01_04 (firefox) timed out at 60_000ms\n\nThese are intermittent failures — they passed in the previous `--reporter=list` run (84 passed). The root issue is UAT environment variability + parallel test execution consuming more resources.\n\nThe real challenge: The UAT environment is slow and variable. My previous list run showed 84/84 passed, but the JSON run shows 81/84.\n\nFor TC-83227 and TC-83228 (edge): Even 45s isn't always enough when UAT is loaded by multiple parallel test instances. I've already set:\n- TC-83227: `test.setTimeout(120_000)` + `toBeVisible({ timeout: 45_000 })`  \n- TC-83228: `test.setTimeout(120_000)` + `waitFor({ timeout: 45_000 })`\n\nBut they still fail at 45s. The issue is that when ALL 4 browsers run simultaneously, the Edge tests compete for UAT resources and take longer.\n\nOptions:\n1. Increase visible timeouts further (60s)\n2. Add `waitForLoadState('networkidle')` before the key interactions in these tests\n3. Reduce parallelism in playwright.config.ts\n\nFor FTC_02_01_04 (firefox) timing out at 60s: This test runs on ALL browsers and usually passes. Firefox is slower. Let me check if it needs a timeout extension too.\n\nActually, looking at the pattern - the tests that are flaking are:\n- Edge: TC-83227, TC-83228 - these now have increased waitFor timeouts but Edge itself might be slower than expected under load\n- Firefox: FTC_02_01_04 - needs timeout extension\n\nThe simplest fix: For the Edge-specific tests, push the key element waitFor timeouts to 60s (from 45s). For FTC_02_01_04, check if it needs a setTimeout.\n\nAlso I should consider: maybe the `reporters=list` run had 84/84 because it happened to run when UAT was less loaded. The issue is environmental.\n\nLet me check FTC_02_01_04 for a setTimeout:\n"}}
