[18:34:16] {"event": "final_response", "content": "All fixes applied and verified. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n---\n\n**Root cause:** All 6 original failures (+ additional ones discovered during re-runs) were caused by **UAT environment latency under parallel browser execution** — Edge, Firefox, and WebKit hydrate Next.js/React/Builder.io pages 2–3× slower than Chromium, especially when 4 browsers run simultaneously.\n\n**Fixes applied:**\n\n| Test | File | Fix |\n|---|---|---|\n| TC-83227 (Edge) | `home-page.spec.ts` | `test.setTimeout(120_000)` + heading `toBeVisible` timeout 30s → 60s |\n| TC-83228 (Edge) | `home-page.spec.ts` | `test.setTimeout(120_000)` + `storesLink.waitFor` 30s → 60s + `networkidle` 8s → 20s |\n| TC-83229 (Edge) | `home-page.spec.ts` | `test.setTimeout(180_000)` (multi-navigation test) |\n| TC-83232 (Chromium + Edge) | Already fixed (incremental scroll loop + 180s timeout) | Confirmed passing |\n| TC-83238 (Firefox + WebKit) | `pdp.spec.ts` | `test.setTimeout(150_000)` + store-selector try/catch fallback (already present) |\n| TC-83240 (Chromium + Edge) | `pages/LoginPage.ts` | `emailInput.waitFor` 15s → 45s + navigate to `/auth/login` directly (already present) |\n| FTC_02_01_02 (Firefox) | `plp.spec.ts` | `test.setTimeout(120_000)` |\n| FTC_02_01_04 (Firefox) | `plp.spec.ts` | `test.setTimeout(120_000)` |\n\n**Final result:** ✅ **84/84 tests passed** across Chromium, Firefox, WebKit, and Edge."}
